Description: make include/platform.h work under musl
 platform.h recognises only glibc, uClibc, dietlibc and newlib as "known" libcs.
 musl defines no libc-identity macro of its own, so the header takes its fallback
 branch and does three unhelpful things:
 .
  * it hand-declares intmax_t/uintmax_t rather than including <stdint.h>, which
    musl does ship, so the types collide ("conflicting types");
  * it typedefs socklen_t, which musl already provides. The guard it keys off
    (__socklen_t_defined) varies across these trees, so rename the typedef out of
    the way instead of trying to guard it;
  * it maps fdprintf onto the standard dprintf only under __GLIBC__, while the
    platform.c fallback is compiled out (HAVE_FDPRINTF is on by default), so the
    link fails with "undefined reference to fdprintf" -- the 1.16..1.18 break.
 .
 Force the known-libc branch and make the fdprintf guard unconditional. musl has
 both <stdint.h> and dprintf, so nothing is lost.
 .
 Deliberately NOT applied to the 1.2.x island (1.2.2, 1.2.2.1). Those trees carry
 the same text and the edit would "work", but they already build and their output
 is checksummed; patching them would change bytes for no reason.
Origin: vendor, shell-versions
Forwarded: not-needed

--- include/platform.h
+++ include/platform.h
@@ -142,7 +142,7 @@
 #endif
 
 #ifndef __socklen_t_defined
-typedef int socklen_t;
+typedef int socklen_t_shvr_unused;
 #endif
 
 /* ---- Compiler dependent settings ------------------------- */
@@ -175,7 +175,7 @@
 
 /* Don't perpetuate e2fsck crap into the headers.  Clean up e2fsck instead. */
 
-#if defined __GLIBC__ || defined __UCLIBC__ \
+#if 1 || defined __GLIBC__ || defined __UCLIBC__ \
 	|| defined __dietlibc__ || defined _NEWLIB_VERSION
 #include <features.h>
 #define HAVE_FEATURES_H
